SIMPLE: bracer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bracer
<hw>Bra"cer</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That
which braces, binds, or makes firm; a band or bandage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A covering to protect the arm of the bowman from the
vibration of the string; also, a brassart.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A medicine, as an astringent or a tonic, which gives
tension or tone to any part of the body.</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brach</ent>⟦br⟧
